== You have been warned ==

{{mbox|type=serious|msg='''Please help <u>''improve''</u> Wikibooks'''.

[[Special:Contributions/{{PAGENAME}}|Recent edits]] you made have not been considered constructive by your fellow contributors. Please use the [[Wikibooks:Sandbox|sandbox]] in the future if you wish to test something out. For a description of the type of content that we do allow, see [[WB:WIW]]. If you have questions about this, or need help, ask at the [[WB:HELP|Reading Room Assistance]] page. Thanks. [[User:AdRiley|AdRiley]] ([[User talk:AdRiley|talk]]) 14:43, 16 March 2008 (UTC)}}

You cannot fix it if you cannot take it apart, so this "book" concentrates on how to disassemble dishwashers.  Some manufacturers make assembly drawings available on the web, but more frequently you have to buy manuals that will be used only once.  Some of the replacement part suppliers have instructions, but this information is somewhat scattered.  So please contribute your experience on how you fixed your dishwasher.

== Contents ==  
#  [[/KitchenAid Repair/Chopper Replacement/]]   
#  [[/Diagnosing a Dishwasher that won't start/]]

