{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Hippocampus| type=Magical Creature| features=Head, forequarters horse, hindqaurters, tail giant fish| appearance=''Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them''}}
== Overview == '''''Hippocampi''''' are the equine equivalent of Muggle "mermaids": forequarters and head of a horse, and tail of a fish.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
The Hippocampus is largely a Mediterranean beast, though a single example was caught off the coast of Scotland by [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Merpeople|Mermen]] in 1949.
== Analysis ==
While the Hippocampus does not appear in the main story, it does appear in the stated from in Muggle mythology. The name has also been used to identify a part of the structure of the brain which is apparently somehow involved with the creation and storage of memories.
